#### **Day 54: Request Body & DTOs**
```markdown
# Day 54: Handling JSON Input with @RequestBody

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. Sending JSON data from Client (Postman) to Server.
2. The `@RequestBody` annotation.
3. Deserialization (JSON -> Java Object).
4. Concept of DTO (Data Transfer Object).

**Learning Summary:**
When creating a user, we can't send all details in the URL. Today I learned to use `@RequestBody` to accept a JSON object inside the HTTP body. I also learned about **DTOs**â€”simple classes used to define what data we expect from the user, keeping our internal database entities safe and separate.

**Code Snippet:**
```java
class UserDTO {
    public String username;
    public String email;
}

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/register")
public class RegistrationController {

    // Input JSON: {"username": "admin", "email": "admin@test.com"}
    @PostMapping
    public String register(@RequestBody UserDTO user) {
        return "Registered User: " + user.username;
    }
}
